<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>ðŸ’¡ Can You Tell AI from Human Writing?</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Read each sample and guess whether it was written by a human or generated by AI</p>
        
        <div class="sample">
            <div class="sample-number">Sample 1: College Application Essay Excerpt</div>
            <div class="sample-text">
                "Throughout my high school journey, I have consistently demonstrated a multifaceted approach to personal growth and academic excellence. My diverse extracurricular involvement, ranging from varsity athletics to community service initiatives, has fostered my development as a well-rounded individual. I am particularly passionate about leveraging my leadership skills to create meaningful impact in my future endeavors, and I believe your esteemed institution provides the optimal environment for achieving my aspirations."
            </div>
            <div class="button-group">
                <button class="choice-btn" data-choice="human">Human</button>
                <button class="choice-btn" data-choice="ai">AI</button>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation">
                <strong>Answer: AI-generated</strong><br>
                <strong>Telltale signs:</strong> Overly formal language, buzzwords like "multifaceted approach" and "esteemed institution," generic phrases that don't reveal specific personality or experiences, and the mechanical way it lists accomplishments without personal connection.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sample">
            <div class="sample-number">Sample 2: Product Review</div>
            <div class="sample-text">
                "Okay, so I was super skeptical about this coffee maker because honestly, who needs another gadget? But my roommate kept leaving grounds everywhere with the old one and I was losing my mind. This thing is actually pretty great - it's way quieter than I expected (thank god, because I make coffee at 6am) and the timer function means I wake up to fresh coffee. Only weird thing is the water reservoir is kind of awkward to fill, but whatever. Would definitely buy again."
            </div>
            <div class="button-group">
                <button class="choice-btn" data-choice="human">Human</button>
                <button class="choice-btn" data-choice="ai">AI</button>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation">
                <strong>Answer: Human-written</strong><br>
                <strong>Human indicators:</strong> Conversational tone with casual language ("Okay, so" and "whatever"), specific personal details (6am coffee, messy roommate), authentic mixed feelings (mostly positive but mentions the awkward water reservoir), and natural speech patterns.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sample">
            <div class="sample-number">Sample 3: Study Tips Blog Post</div>
            <div class="sample-text">
                "Effective study strategies are essential for academic success in today's competitive educational landscape. Students should implement a variety of evidence-based techniques to optimize their learning outcomes. These include creating structured study schedules, utilizing active recall methods, and maintaining proper nutrition and sleep hygiene. Additionally, forming study groups can enhance comprehension through collaborative learning experiences while also developing important interpersonal skills."
            </div>
            <div class="button-group">
                <button class="choice-btn" data-choice="human">Human</button>
                <button class="choice-btn" data-choice="ai">AI</button>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation">
                <strong>Answer: AI-generated</strong><br>
                <strong>Telltale signs:</strong> Very formal and academic tone, generic advice without specific examples, buzzword-heavy language ("evidence-based techniques," "optimize learning outcomes"), and lacks the personal voice you'd expect from someone sharing study tips from experience.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sample">
            <div class="sample-number">Sample 4: Social Media Post About Campus Life</div>
            <div class="sample-text">
                "just finished my first organic chem exam and i think my brain melted?? ðŸ˜­ spent literally 8 hours in the library yesterday and still forgot what SN2 reactions were. at least the girl next to me looked just as confused lol. time for some serious coffee and maybe crying. why did i think pre-med was a good idea again"
            </div>
            <div class="button-group">
                <button class="choice-btn" data-choice="human">Human</button>
                <button class="choice-btn" data-choice="ai">AI</button>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation">
                <strong>Answer: Human-written</strong><br>
                <strong>Human indicators:</strong> Authentic emotional expression, specific academic details (SN2 reactions, organic chem), casual social media language with emojis, self-deprecating humor, and the genuine stress/doubt that students actually experience.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sample">
            <div class="sample-number">Sample 5: Email to Professor</div>
            <div class="sample-text">
                "Dear Professor Johnson,<br><br>I hope this email finds you well. I am writing to inquire about the upcoming research opportunities in your laboratory. As a dedicated student with a strong academic record, I believe I would be a valuable addition to your research team. I have thoroughly reviewed your recent publications and am particularly interested in your work on cellular mechanisms. I would be grateful for the opportunity to discuss how my skills and interests align with your current projects.<br><br>Thank you for your time and consideration.<br><br>Best regards,<br>Student"
            </div>
            <div class="button-group">
                <button class="choice-btn" data-choice="human">Human</button>
                <button class="choice-btn" data-choice="ai">AI</button>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation">
                <strong>Answer: Human-written</strong><br>
                <strong>Human indicators:</strong> While formal, this has the genuine tone of a student trying to sound professional. The slight awkwardness ("I hope this email finds you well") and generic but earnest language is typical of students writing their first professional emails. AI tends to be either more polished or more obviously formulaic.
            </div>
        </div>

        <button class="submit-btn" onclick="checkAnswers()" disabled>Submit Your Guesses</button>
        
        <div class="results">
            <div class="score"></div>
            <p>AI-generated content often has telltale signs like overly formal language, generic phrasing, lack of specific personal details, and a "perfect" but impersonal tone. Human writing usually includes conversational elements, specific experiences, natural imperfections, and authentic emotional expression.</p>
            <button class="reset-btn" onclick="resetQuiz()">Try Again</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        const samples = document.querySelectorAll('.sample');
        const submitBtn = document.querySelector('.submit-btn');
        const results = document.querySelector('.results');
        const correctAnswers = ['ai', 'human', 'ai', 'human', 'human'];
        let userAnswers = [];

        // Add click handlers to choice buttons
        samples.forEach((sample, index) => {
            const buttons = sample.querySelectorAll('.choice-btn');
            buttons.forEach(btn => {
                btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    // Remove selected class from all buttons in this sample
                    buttons.forEach(b => b.classList.remove('selected'));
                    // Add selected class to clicked button
                    btn.classList.add('selected');
                    // Store the answer
                    userAnswers[index] = btn.dataset.choice;
                    
                    // Check if all questions are answered
                    if (userAnswers.filter(answer => answer).length === 5) {
                        submitBtn.disabled = false;
                    }
                });
            });
        });

        function checkAnswers() {
            let score = 0;
            
            samples.forEach((sample, index) => {
                const buttons = sample.querySelectorAll('.choice-btn');
                const explanation = sample.querySelector('.explanation');
                const userChoice = userAnswers[index];
                const correctChoice = correctAnswers[index];
                
                buttons.forEach(btn => {
                    btn.classList.remove('selected');
                    if (btn.dataset.choice === correctChoice) {
                        btn.classList.add('correct');
                    } else if (btn.dataset.choice === userChoice && userChoice !== correctChoice) {
                        btn.classList.add('incorrect');
                    }
                });
                
                if (userChoice === correctChoice) {
                    score++;
                }
                
                explanation.style.display = 'block';
            });
            
            // Show results
            const scoreElement = document.querySelector('.score');
            scoreElement.textContent = `You got ${score} out of 5 correct!`;
            results.style.display = 'block';
            submitBtn.style.display = 'none';
            
            // Add performance message
            let message = '';
            if (score === 5) message = 'Perfect! You have a great eye for detecting AI-generated content.';
            else if (score >= 3) message = 'Good work! You\'re developing strong critical evaluation skills.';
            else message = 'Don\'t worry - distinguishing AI from human writing takes practice!';
            
            results.querySelector('p').innerHTML = message + '<br><br>' + results.querySelector('p').innerHTML;
        }

        function resetQuiz() {
            userAnswers = [];
            
            samples.forEach(sample => {
                const buttons = sample.querySelectorAll('.choice-btn');
                buttons.forEach(btn => {
                    btn.classList.remove('selected', 'correct', 'incorrect');
                });
                sample.querySelector('.explanation').style.display = 'none';
            });
            
            results.style.display = 'none';
            submitBtn.style.display = 'block';
            submitBtn.disabled = true;
        }
    </script>
</body>
